==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emend
<hw>E*mend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Emended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Emending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>emendare</ets>;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>menda</ets>, <ets>mendum</ets>, fault, blemish:
cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧mender</ets>. Cf. <er>Amend</er>,
<er>Mend</er>.]</ety> <def>To purge of faults; to make better; to
correct; esp., to make corrections in (a literary work); to alter for
the better by textual criticism, generally verbal.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To amend; correct; improve; better; reform;
rectify. See <er>Amend</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emendable</ent>⟦br⟧
